results.description:
The Fountain of Goof F.O.G. Tv Network - General Tosspital 

Season 1

Episode 1:  The show begins with a wealthy family living within a scenic 300-acre remote Texas ranch called South Pork.  The Suings’ clan chef, housekeeping staff and gardners are busily planning and preparing their main humdinger bar-b-que bash for this Labor Day weekend.

Episode 2:  J. Kar and wife Nellie graciously stroll down the mansion’s spiral staircase wearing their favorite second-hand store apparel.  They quietly gather at the breakfast table with Ma, Pa, Cousin Sara, Auntie em…and of course Grandma.  Suddenly, there’s an unexpected loud bang, a shrill scream, and glass breaking…then...a thump…as though something collapsed to the ground.

Eyes widen…everyone jumps out of their seats and run towards the scene of the rind…only to surprisingly discover…

Episode 3:  The next scene opens with the Suing’s clan sitting at General Tosspital’s emergency room…arguing, bickering among themselves as to Who…Who…Who let the Hog out of South Pork’s mansion.  The attending doctor slowly walks thru the hospital’s double doors…removes his protective blue facemask and announces:

“I’m very, very sorry…but…He’s pork rinds now”.  “We tried to save him, but…

“Perhaps…you would like to donate his organs for a Ground Hog’s Day celebration?”

After a brief moment…J. Kar Suing yelled,

“Nellie...Again?!!!”  There’s another holiday gone to the HOGS!”

Stay tuned for previews of Season 2…titled: South Pork’s - Who Dunnit Murder Mystery.  

(the scene closes with a picture of several hams smiling...standing in front of General Tosspital’s main entrance building)


Esther Monsalve
